Minju Joson Ridicules Press Conference on Iraqi Situation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- The fact-finding group made up of south Korean "national assemblymen" was reported to have called a press conference recently upon its return home from Iraq. At the conference it asserted that "the situation in Iraq was safer than anticipated" and "Iraqis were in the mood of welcoming south Koreans."
 In this regard Minju Joson today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
On November 30, a few days after the press conference members of the south Korean "Omu Electrical Company" in Iraq were attacked by Iraqi resistance forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The attack on the members of the south Korean electrical company was gainsaying what was stated by "national assemblymen" at the "press conference," the Iraqi people's bitterness towards south Korea is clearly evidenced by the fact that after the south Korean authorities' decision on the additional dispatch of combat forces to Iraq, a staff member of the south Korean "embassy" there was abducted by Iraqi resistance forces and it is deluged with threatening phone messages and letters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The account of the "press conference" held by the "National Assembly" fact-finding group of south Korea and the report presented by it are now rebuffed by public circles of south Korea for misrepresenting the reality in Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not only the south Koreans but the Iraqis are opposed to south Korea's additional troop dispatch to Iraq. This dispatch is an act of infringing upon the dignity and sovereignty of the south Korean people and offering young south Koreans as bullet-shields for the U.S. imperialists.

Repeal of Troop Dispatch to Iraq Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity reportedly made public a statement titled "Repeal Troop Dispatch to Iraq Which Kills All Our People" on December 1.
 The statement said that two of the south Korean civilians who had a contract to build a power transmission tower of a U.S. corporation in Iraq were shot to death and two others wounded on November 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement charged that the "inspection group of the National Assembly", which had been to Iraq, saw only what was shown by the U.S. troops and, back home, told a lie that the public peace of Iraq was stable, not referring to the fact that the resisting forces were raining shells upon them on the spot and waging a battle with the U.S. troops. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement demanded that the authorities and the political power stop telling a lie deceiving the people and withdraw the already dispatched units at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Democratic Workers' Party in a commentary charged that despite the injury to south Korean civilians in Iraq the "government" clarified again its stand to dispatch troops and the "Ministry of National Defense" insisted on the dispatch of a commando unit, which is a reverse decision. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities should not turn away from the demand of the people but withdraw the decision on troop dispatch at once, the commentary said, stressing: The Democratic Workers' Party, together with all the people, will make all efforts for the withdrawal of troop dispatch.

Abrogation of "Security Law" Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for Abolition of the "Security Law" consisting of more than 230 civic and public organizations in south Korea reportedly held a press conference in Seoul on December 1 and declared a massive struggle for abrogation of the evil law.
 At the press conference a report on the situation of applying the "security law" was made and then an open questionnaire to national assemblymen and other politicians made public and a press release read out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press release said that the organization would start a powerful struggle to make 2004 the first year of the abolition of the "security law". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the Pusan Solidarity for Abolition of the "Security Law" held a "press conference of civic and public organizations in Pusan for abolition of the security law and checking the enactment of the law on combating terrorism and against the retrogressive revision of the law on assembly and demonstration" at the plaza of Pusan Railway Station. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the General Student Council of Kyonggi University made public a statement on December 1 and said that it would struggle until the "security law" is abolished. The statement stressed: Let's pool our efforts to make a world free from the "security law."

"Day of Korea" Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Functions were held in Turkey from Nov. 11 to 24 on the occasion of the "Day of Korea".
 A lecture, film show, friendly gathering and the cultural evening were held at a hall of the Fine Art and Arts Museum of the Ministry of Culture of Turkey on Nov. 11 to be followed by functions in different cities to mark the day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the functions including a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Turkey, referred to the advantages of the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il, the single-hearted unity of the Korean people united close around him and their heroic struggle against the U.S. imperialists, reiterating their resolution to intensify the movement for solidarity with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films were screened and colorful performances were given at the functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Nov. 13 members of the Grand National Assembly of Turkey including its deputy speaker and officials concerned visited the venues of functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deputy speaker said that Turkey would make positive efforts to develop the friendly relations with the people of the DPRK, accusing the U.S. of escalating the tensions on the Korean peninsula.

Friendly Meeting Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- A friendly meeting with staff members of the Indonesian embassy here was held at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition on Dec. 4 on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of the treaty on technical and cultural cooperation between the governments of the DPRK and Indonesia.
 Present on invitation were Barita Siburian, charge d'affaires ad interim, and staff members of the Indonesian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Also present there were Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Mun Myong Sok, first vice-chairman of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee of the DPRK, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants looked round with keen interest Kimilsungias and Kimjongilias and conversed with one another on the need to boost the friendly relations between the two countries. They deepened the friendship, singing songs of the two countries.

Ecuadorian Party Leader on Friendly and Cooperative Relations with WPK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Gustavo Teran Acosta, national leader of the People's Democratic Movement of Ecuador (PDME), on Nov. 30 met and had a talk with a delegation of the Workers' Party of Korea led by Deputy Department Director Pak Kyong Son on a visit to Ecuador.
 Saying that his party has gained firm confidence in the victory of socialism from the heroic struggle of the WPK and the Korean people to unswervingly defend the dignity of the country and socialism, daringly militating against the U.S. which is styling itself "the only superpower", the national leader stated: The PDME will make assiduous efforts to learn from the rich experience the WPK has achieved in party building and its activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said it was a great honor and pride of the PDME to develop friendly and cooperative relations with the WPK led by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation of the WPK also met Ecuadorian political figures including the general secretary of the Coordination Committee of the Social Party of Latin America and the acting national leader of the January 21 Patriotic Socialist Party of Ecuador.

Cuban Army Day Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Giraldo Abreu Morales, military attache of the Cuban embassy here, hosted a reception at the embassy Thursday evening on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of the revolutionary armed forces of Cuba.
 Present on invitation there were Kim Sang Ik, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, generals and officers of the Korean People's Army and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Esteban Lobaina Romero, Cuban ambassador, and staff members of the Cuban embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Friendly Meeting Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Wojciech Kaluza, Polish ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a friendly meeting at the embassy yesterday on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the DPRK and Poland.
 Present on invitation were Hong Son Ok, vice-chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Polish embassy officials were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants appreciated the Polish feature film "In a Desert and Jungle" and deepened friendly feelings, conversing with each other on further developing the friendly relations between the two countries.

Development of China-DPRK Friendship Stressed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Wu Guanzheng, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China who is also secretary of the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Party, met a delegation of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland led by Director of the Secretariat Jo Kyu Il at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing on Dec. 3.
 The long-standing Sino-Korean friendship was personally provided and brought into bloom by the leaders of old generation of the two countries and sealed in blood in the joint struggle of the two peoples against the Japanese and U.S. imperialists, the secretary said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stating that it is the immovable policy of the Chinese party and government to develop the Sino-Korean friendship, he said mutual visits of the leaders of the two countries in the new century instilled fresh vitality into the development of the relations between China and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new leadership of China, he said, will continue to pursue the friendly policy toward the DPRK and develop the relations with it and China will make tireless efforts to lift the relations of Sino-Korean friendship to a new height in the spirit of "inheritance of tradition, aspiration after the future, good-neighborliness and friendship and strengthening of cooperation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China supports the improvement of relations between the north and the south of Korea and their independent and peaceful reunification under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are pleased to see the Korean people achieving successes in various fields under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il, he said, hoping that they would create a happier life in the future.

U.S. Reckless Arms Build-up Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- U.S. Congress recently made a final approval of the bill on military expenditure for the fiscal 2004 amounting to more than 401 billion dollars and U.S. President Bush signed it.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. approved record-breaking defense budget for the fiscal 2004 is a blatant challenge to the trend of the times in the new century towards independence, peace and disarmament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And it is a criminal move to chill the unanimous desire and aspiration of humankind to live in a new stable and peaceful world free from any danger of nuclear war and arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a serious attention is that the new bill lifted a ban on the research into low-yield nukes and those capable of penetrating underground, which has been in force for scores of years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bellicose Bush ruling quarters keen on hegemony and world domination are going mad with the arms build-up, pursuing the adventurous line of strength and iron-fisted policy in contravention of the aspiration of humankind, world public opinion and the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. defense budget for the fiscal 2001 reached 310 billion U.S. dollars much bigger than that of the Clinton administration. And its defense budget for the fiscal 2002 was 343 billion U.S. dollars, 33 billion dollars bigger than that. The defense budget for the fiscal 2003 ran into over 379 billion U.S. dollars. This is equivalent to 40 percent of the total amount of the world military expenditure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The strategic aim sought by the U.S. in its madcap arms buildup is to retain its military supremacy in a bid to stifle those anti-imperialist independent countries incurring its displeasure by means of military intervention, military terrorism and war, seize major areas of natural resources and military strategic importance, establish an American-style iron-fisted order in the world and thus build a unipolar world dominated by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This U.S. arms build-up may spark the second worldwide arms race as this policy is bound to lead to arms buildup, military intervention and war of aggression.

Miracles of Songun Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Nine years have passed since leader Kim Jong Il left the first great footprints of his Songun leadership at a post of the Korean People's Army surrounded by young pine trees on the New Year of Juche 84 (1995).
 In this period, the Korean people have created a great epic of heroic feats which others would be unable to perform even in centuries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These miracles of Songun Korea praised by the world people as "myth of human history" include the blasting of the "fiction of collapse of north Korea," leap to a possessor of earth satellite and start of the grand march for building a prosperous powerful nation, adoption of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and repatriation of 63 unconverted long-term prisoners, land rezoning of over 200,000 hectares in a matter of a few years, excavation of the Kaechon-Lake Thaesong Canal stretching over 150 km, emergence of a world "marathon queen," the creation of the grand mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang" acclaimed as the acme of human culture, Kim Jong Il's foreign tour covering more than 50,000 ri that shook the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists, reactionaries and mouthpieces on the payroll of imperialism set afloat a hundred and one rumors, crying with bravo that "the 'destruction' of north Korea is a matter of time" and "socialism will disappear soon on the earth with the 'collapse' of north Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "fiction of the destruction of north Korea" about which the Western media shouted themselves hoarse went to pieces in every step of Kim Jong Il's unceasing journey of Songun leadership for 9 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, a small country, put a satellite on the orbit in the first launch entirely with its own technique and wisdom in the difficult days of arduous long march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the launch of satellite as a signal for building a prosperous powerful nation, the DPRK started the grand march towards the majestic goal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical summit meeting of the north and the south and adoption of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration were greatest event that set off a storm of sensation at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 63 unconverted long-term prisoners came back at a time to the socialist motherland. This was an auspicious event of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On May 4, Juche 87 (1998), land-rezoning of gigantic scale was announced in Taebaek-ri, Changdo County, Kangwon Province. In the following five years at least 236,360 hectares of crop fields have been rezoned across the country, bring tremendous changes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The over 150km-long canal tens of meters wide from Taegak-ri, Kaechon City, South Phyongan Province, to Lake Thaesong in Kangso District, Nampho City, is a monumental creation of eternal value built by the Korean army and people in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On August 29, Juche 88 (1999) Jong Song Ok, the DPRK woman marathoner, carried away gold medal at the women's marathon race of the 7th International Athletic Championships held in Sevilla, Spain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Great was the stir created by the grand Gymnastic Display and Artistic Performance "Arirang" performed by over 100,000 persons that opened at May Day Stadium in Pyongyang on April 29, Juche 91 (2002). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Juche 90 (2001) the world was aboil with "Kim Jong Il Impact" and "Kim Jong Il Storm". Kim Jong Il made a long journey of more than 50,000 ri in Russia from July 26 to August 18 that year to perform an immortal exploit peculiar in the histories of the DPRK-Russia relations and world politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These miracles of Songun Korea are, indeed, a great pride of our sun's nation.

Achievements Made in Literature and Art
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 5 (KCNA) -- Great successes have been made in the fields of literature and art in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea this year.
 The Merited Chorus of the Korean People's Army, which significantly decorated leader Kim Jong Il's birthday, February 16, with the chorus suite "Long Journey of Songun Leadership", gave wonderful performances to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the Korean people's victory in the war and the 55th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the concert marking the war victory day it demonstrated the Korean people's determination and will to win a greater victory if another war is unleashed in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many feature films of high ideological and artistic value have been produced this year. Among them are "Our Life," "Mother's Happiness," "Ding of Love," "Notes of a Woman Soldier" and "This Is Where My Life Was Settled." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Successors," "Chol Pass" and other light comedies were created and the 1,000th performance of the revolutionary opera "The Fate of a Self-defence Corps Man" was given successfully. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Women's instrumental ensemble of the Mansudae Art Troupe, kayagum ensemble of the KPA Song and Dance Ensemble and oungum ensemble of the Song and Dance Ensemble of the Ministry of People's Security and other art groups considered to be national treasure have become all the more seasoned in the ideological and artistic respect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's masterpieces also include the full-length novel "Song of Humankind", a sequel to the series "Immortal History", and "Arms", a sequel to "Immortal Leadership", songs "Motherland Dear to My Life", "My Dear Country" and "If I am Asked to Sing of the Fatherland," and poems "What Is the Country Glorified with?" "Victorious July 27 Declares" and "By Ourselves, by Our Nation Itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The publication of "Complete Collection of Korean Songs" which contains thousands of songs is one of signal successes registered in the literary and art fields this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great progress has been made in the fine arts, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A Korean jewel picture won the top prize and a medal at the Inter Kamen (International Exhibition of Stones and Stone Processing Technology).
